Commentary: Luke Ronchi is gone first ball! Full just outside off, and Ronchi goes for an expansive cover drive. Thick outside edge, and pouched by first slip diving to his right. What a start for LQ! A golden duck for Luke Ronch, would you believe it

Dismissal_text: L Ronchi c Haris Sohail b Shaheen Shah Afridi 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: full on off, and he crunches a drive from near his toes. Through to cover point on the bounce
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Salt, no run

Commentary: full onm off, and he prods forward before driving with the bat's open face through cover! Damn, this outfield is fasttttt
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Salt, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball, angling away after landing on off. He pushes at this off the back foot, and edges it down to third man
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Salt, 1 run

Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Salt, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball on off, and jagging away after pitching. Tries to flat-bat a shot through the off side, but under-edges it towards mid off
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Salt, no run

Commentary: full on leg, and he tries to nudge it fine. Padded towards short fine leg, as they pinch a single in the process. Umpire gives it as runs though
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Salt, 1 run

Commentary: punched! Length ball moving away from Delport, and he rides the bounce to firmly strike this through the off side
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Delport, FOUR runs

Commentary: muscled! And that's the day's first six. Full on middle, and Delport walks across to the off side, before slapping this over midwicket!
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Delport, SIX runs

Commentary: length ball, just wide outside off, and cut fine past short third man! Expensive
Commentary_short: Rahat Ali to Delport, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on off, and the googly spins inwards. Defended off the front foot
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Salt, no run

Commentary: full and wide outside off, and Salt takes a huge step towards the ball. Tries to lift it over cover, but he's toe-ended the shot in the air. Mid-off gets under it, and makes no mistake! Sandeep strikes right away!

Dismissal_text: PD Salt c Haris Sohail b Lamichhane 10 (8b 2x4 0x6) SR: 125.00

Commentary: full on leg, and the googly comes into his pads. Tucked away to short fine leg

Commentary: half-tracker on middle, and turning towards off stump. He rocks back, and pulls along the ground to deep midwicket

Commentary: full on middle, and angling into his pads. Delport closes his bat's face, and whips this right over short fine leg!

Commentary: full just outside off, and Delport has gone for a golf swing. Tries to smack this over long-on, but the shot has been toe-ended. In the air for ages, and Sohail Akhtar runs towards the boundary from midwicket, but the ball pops out of his hand, and Delport survives. Dropped!

Commentary: low full toss on off, and he drills a straight drive to mid-off
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Delport, no run

Commentary: short! Fast and precise on off, and Delport ducks to take cover
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Delport, no run

Commentary: hammered! And this one has been timed beautifully. Ball hits the digital scorecard. Full on off, but Delport makes room, and opens his stance, before clobbering this (baseball-style) over long on. Wowza

Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Delport, SIX runs

Commentary: length ball on off, and turning into Delport. Clipped off the back foot to square leg
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Delport, no run

Commentary: full outside off, and Walton takes a big stride forward to block Lamichhane's final ball

Commentary: length ball, wide outside off, and cut off the back foot to third man for a single

Commentary: half-tracker on middle from around the wicket. Pulled along the ground to deep square leg

Commentary: skiddy ball, full outside off, and driven to the fielder at cover

Commentary: slower ball, short on off, and he muscles a cut past the fielder at cover. He gets a hand to it, thereby slowing the ball's pace

Commentary: length ball on off, and angling in. Nudged off his pads to the vacant mid-wicket region
Commentary_short: Wiese to Walton, 1 run

Commentary: full on off, and he mistimes a straight drive to long off for a single

Commentary: full on off, and mistimed to long on
Commentary_short: Wiese to Walton, 1 run

Commentary: reverse swept through the infield! Full on leg, but he picked the googly early, and pierces the tiny gap between short third man and point

Commentary: length ball on leg, and the googly is punched off the back foot to long on

Commentary: slider outside off, and Walton cuts off the back foot to short third man
Commentary_short: Lamichhane to Walton, no run

Commentary: length ball on off, and the ball that's sliding inwards is punched off the back foot to long on

Commentary: yorker outside leg, and he taps a drive to mid-off

Commentary: length ball, wide outside off, and punched to cover for a single

Rauf apologises right away, and the umpire has a chat with the bowler. Not sure why he was aiming at the stumps in the first place. Delport was well in. Frustration, perhaps?

Commentary: full and wide outside off, and he drills a flat-batted cut to deep point

Commentary: back of a length on off, and he goes for a pull. Ball stays slighty low, and goes over off stump to Ronchi. Just five runs off that over. Priceless

Commentary: length ball on leg stump, and skidding through. Tries to flick towards the leg side, but the ball hits his knee roll

Commentary: slower blal, full on off, and he times this straight drive well. Just past the bowler's left, and mid-on runs to his left to slide and stop the ball. Parries it towards mid-off, but saves the boundary

Commentary: back of a length, wide outside off, and the cut-shot finds the fielder at point
Commentary_short: Rumman Raees to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: yorker on leg, and he inside-edges a shot right into his boots. Ball rolls away to the off side

Commentary: length ball, wide outside off, and he drags this slower ball in front of midwicket! Ball dribbles away to the leg-side fence for four. Well improvised by Wessels!

Commentary: yorker angling into leg stump, and flicked off his toes to deep midwicket. No ball though so that's a free-hit

Commentary: full on middle, and he drills a shot to mid-on. Dot

Commentary: length ball on off, and he splices a pull to midwicket

Commentary: length ball on off, and he tries to flat-bat a shot over long on. Toe-ends the shot, and that's been taken by the long-on fielder sliding in! He claims it's 'out' but the umpires want to check. They ask Fakhar to wait. Soft signal 'out'. Big moment in the game as we wait for the TV umpire. Replays suggest that the fielder had his hands under the ball while sliding in from long-on. Looks ominous for Fakhar... and yep, he's got to go! Superb high-pressure catch by Salt, and Fakhar's 20-ball innings comes to a close
Commentary_short: Faheem Ashraf to Fakhar Zaman, OUT
Dismissal_text: Fakhar Zaman c Salt b Faheem Ashraf 38 (20b 4x4 3x6) SR: 190.00

Commentary: length ball on off, and cramped for space. Wessels looks to punch towards the off side, but the shot's been inside-edged to the fine-leg boundary!
